.SH NAME
lpfc_find_vport_by_vpid \- Find a vport on a HBA through vport identifier
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct lpfc_vport *" lpfc_find_vport_by_vpid
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "uint16_t vpi "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to lpfc hba data structure.
.IP "vpi" 12
the physical host virtual N_Port identifier.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine finds a vport on a HBA (referred by \fIphba\fP) through a
\fIvpi\fP. The function walks the HBA's vport list and returns the address
of the vport with the matching \fIvpi\fP.

Return code
NULL - No vport with the matching \fIvpi\fP found
Otherwise - Address to the vport with the matching \fIvpi\fP.
